channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: North Carolina Officer Kenneth Battle-Hay Saves the Life of 4-Week Old Baby
Ted Cruz calls for death penalty if 2 illegal immigrants accused of killing 12-year-old girl are convicted
item.description: Sen. Ted Cruz said two illegal immigrants accused of killing a Houston girl this week should get the death penalty if they are convicted.

item.title: N.J. Charges Against Norcross Brothers 'Entirely Baseless,' Lawyers Say
item.description: The recent charges against New Jersey Democrat political kingmaker George Norcross III, his brother Phil, and four other defendants are nothing more than a "political attack masquerading as a criminal case," attorneys for the accused said Friday.

item.title: HEROES: Quick Thinking by 3 Fishermen Leads to Them Rescuing 38 Pooches From Drowning
Texas Lt. Gov. Dan Patrick pledges to pass Ten Commandments bill after Louisiana passes similar law
item.description: Texas Lt. Gov. Dan Patrick on Friday blamed a fellow Republican for not passing a law requiring public school classrooms to display the Ten Commandments.

item.title: Matt Schlapp to Newsmax: Trump's Green Card Plan Savvy
item.description: American Conservative Union Chair Matt Schlapp told Newsmax on Friday that it takes a businessman like Donald Trump to solve the more intricate challenges that the country faces - keeping highly skilled workers in the country, for one.

item.title: Incredible: 'Just Stop Oil' Defaced Stonehenge, American Bros Showed Up and Relentlessly Bullied Them
US v Trump: First day of Florida hearing wraps in classified docs case
item.description: President Trump's legal team was in court Friday arguing that Special Counsel Jack Smith was appointed illegally, meaning that the classified documents case should be tossed.

item.title: GOP Convention Security Plan Permits Guns in Outer Perimeter
item.description: People will be permitted to carry firearms just blocks removed from the Republican National Convention in Milwaukee next month, according to a security plan law enforcement authorities released Friday, The Hill reported.

item.title: Judge Judy Stuns CNN's Wallace With Quip on Trump Verdict, How Violent Manhattan Has Become Under Bragg
Fox News Politics: No Guns for Abusers
item.description: The latest updates from the 2024 campaign trail, exclusive interviews and more Fox News politics content

item.title: Rep. Donalds to Newsmax: Some Republicans Ready to Slash Govt
item.description: If former President Donald Trump is elected, some Republicans are prepared to put a bill on his desk that slashes the government by 50% to get U.S. debt under control, said Rep. Byron Donalds, R-S.C.

item.title: Putin's War, Week 121. Putin Threatens, Zelensky Negotiates, and the White House Sends Lots of Missiles
SCOTUS rejects woman's claim she has constitutional right to visa for husband with MS-13 ties
item.description: An American citizen who sued to get her noncitizen MS-13-member husband a visa has no constitutional liberty interest to such a lawsuit, the Supreme Court ruled Friday.

item.title: VP Hopefuls to Attend Watch Party for Trump-Biden Debate
item.description: A host of vice presidential hopefuls will descend on Atlanta next week for a watch party and fundraiser for Republican presumptive nominee Donald Trump's first presidential debate against President Joe Biden, the Washington Examiner reported.
